@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>Enphase OAuth Token Manager</h1>

<div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading">Welcome to the OAuth Token Manager!</h4>
    <p>This is a dedicated application for obtaining Enphase API tokens through OAuth authentication.</p>
    <hr>
    <p class="mb-0">Use this app to:</p>
    <ul class="mt-2">
        <li>Authenticate with Enphase cloud APIs</li>
        <li>Obtain API access tokens</li>
        <li>Copy tokens for use in other applications</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card mt-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">How it works</h5>
        <div class="card-text">
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Navigate to OAuth:</strong> Click the "OAuth" link in the menu</li>
                <li><strong>Start OAuth Flow:</strong> Begin authentication with Enphase</li>
                <li><strong>Authorize Access:</strong> Complete authorization on Enphase website</li>
                <li><strong>Copy Token:</strong> Return here to copy your access token</li>
                <li><strong>Use in Apps:</strong> Paste token into MAUI app or WASM app settings</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card mt-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">Architecture</h5>
        <p class="card-text">
            This OAuth app runs server-side and loads configuration from appsettings.json.
            The main MAUI and WASM applications can run standalone after receiving tokens from this service.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
    <a href="/oauth" class="btn btn-primary">Start OAuth Process</a>
</div>
